<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[120,1225,835,1310]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
COMMENTS: A highly polyphagous species, taken/reared from 42 species of flowers in 16 families (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz, H. J." box="[226,397,1247,1273]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref25620" refString="Schmitz, H. J. 2010. Genetica, ecologia e evolucao de drosofilideos (Insecta, Diptera) associados a flores. Ph. D. dissertation, Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, Brazil." type="book" year="2010">Schmitz, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Like 
<taxonomicName box="[473,619,1247,1273]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis box="[473,619,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">D. bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species can, with care, be cultured on standard lab medium (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz, H. J." box="[278,452,1284,1310]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref25620" refString="Schmitz, H. J. 2010. Genetica, ecologia e evolucao de drosofilideos (Insecta, Diptera) associados a flores. Ph. D. dissertation, Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, Brazil." type="book" year="2010">Schmitz, 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
